@startuml
!theme cerulean
' skinparam dpi 300
skinparam svgDimensionStyle false
skinparam backgroundColor white
title NexisOS Package Install – Updated High-Level Flow

actor User
participant "CLI / API\n(Frontend)" as CLI
participant "TOML Parser\n(Config Loader)" as Parser
participant "Dependency Resolver\n(Graph + DAG Builder)" as Resolver
participant "Hash Engine\n(BLAKE3)" as Hasher
participant "Content Store\n(Immutable CAS)" as Store
participant "Mutable Env Manager\n(Overlays/VFS)" as Mutable
participant "Generation Builder\n(Projected FHS)" as Builder
participant "Activation Manager\n(/system Symlink)" as Activate

== User Request ==
User -> CLI : install packageA
CLI -> Parser : load TOML config

== Dependency Resolution ==
Parser -> Resolver : parsed config + dependencies
Resolver -> Resolver : normalize DAG
Resolver -> Hasher : compute GraphID

== Package Processing ==
loop For each package
    Resolver -> Hasher : hash file contents → ContentID
    Hasher --> Store : lookup ContentID
    alt Exists in Store
        Store --> Resolver : reuse existing object (dedup)
    else
        Hasher -> Store : insert object (chunked CAS, hybrid fixed+rolling)
        Store --> Resolver : object stored
    end
    Resolver -> Hasher : compute PackageID (ContentIDs + GraphID)
    Hasher --> Store : lookup PackageID
    alt Exists
        Store --> Builder : reuse package
    else
        Store --> Builder : record new package
    end
end

== Parallel Execution ==
par Binary Download (if available)
    Builder -> Store : fetch via HTTP/3 or BitTorrent/IPFS
    Store -> Store : verify BLAKE3 hash & chunk integrity
    Store --> Builder : download complete
end

par Source Build (if needed)
    Builder -> Builder : hermetic sandboxed build\n(namespaces + cgroups)
    Builder -> Store : write chunks with dedup-on-insert
    Store --> Builder : build complete
end

== Mutable Environment Setup ==
Builder -> Mutable : configure mutable work dirs\n(e.g., Java security dirs)
Mutable -> Mutable : setup overlays/VFS
Mutable -> Builder : link immutable + mutable paths

== Generation Construction ==
Builder -> Builder : build projected FHS rootfs
Builder -> Store : compute GenerationID (sorted PackageIDs)
Builder --> Store : record Generation

== Activation ==
Builder -> Activate : point /system to new generation
Activate -> CLI : activation success
CLI -> User : packageA installed ✓

note over Hasher
**Hasher / Identity:**
• ContentID = blake3(file)
• GraphID = blake3(normalized DAG)
• PackageID = hash(ContentIDs + GraphID)
• GenerationID = hash(sorted PackageIDs)
• Enables binary reuse & minimal rebuild
end note

note over Store
**Content Store:**
• Immutable CAS
• Chunked hybrid (fixed + rolling)
• Bloom filter pre-checks
• ROAR bitmap for references
• Zstd/LZ4 compression optional
• Insert-time deduplication (no global scan)
end note

note over Mutable
**Mutable Manager:**
• Overlays for work dirs
• VFS for paths like Java security dirs
• Ensures mutable state without nix-ld
end note

note over Builder
**Generation Builder:**
• Projected FHS rootfs
• SELinux labels applied
• Only rebuild changed packages
• Minimal rollback via symlink
end note

@enduml
